    <div class="section">
      <h2>Ingredients</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>1 and 3/4 cups (220g) all-purpose flour</li>
        <li>1/2 cup (45g) unsweetened cocoa powder</li>
        <li>1 tsp baking powder</li>
        <li>1/2 tsp baking soda</li>
        <li>1 cup (240ml) buttermilk (or milk + 1 tsp vinegar)</li>
        <li>1 cup (170g) chocolate chips or chunks</li>
        <li>2 large eggs</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
      <h2>Method</h2>
      <ol>
        <li>Preheat the oven to 180°C (350°F). Line a muffin tray with paper liners.</li>
        <li>In a bowl, sift together flour, cocoa powder, baking powder, baking soda, and salt.</li>
        <li>In another large bowl, whisk eggs and sugar until light and fluffy.</li>
        <li>Add oil, buttermilk, and vanilla to the egg mixture and mix well.</li>
        <li>Gradually fold in the dry ingredients until just combined (don’t overmix). Gently stir in the chocolate chips.</li>
        <li>Bake for 18–22 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean.</li>
      </ol>
